Phillip Schofield and Dame Kelly Holmes joined the likes of Gok Wan, Lorraine Kelly and Alison Hammond in London to mark the 50th anniversary of the UK’s first Pride parade.  The group walked in multi-coloured t-shirts with “ITV Pride” emblazoned on them as they made their way from Hyde Park Corner to Whitehall.In clips shared to Instagram, they looked like they were having a whale of a time.Kelly filmed part of their march and while sharing the screen with Phil, told her followers: “Guys, it’s our first Pride... I am totally immersed in it.“I did it, I’m here, we are live at Pride!” More to follow...